<button class="accordion">What is the meaning of valid consent?</button>
<div class="panel"> 
<p>A valid consent means that the person understands the information given to them and have the capacity to make an informed, voluntary decision.</p>
</div>

<button class="accordion">What is implied consent?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Implied consent occurs through the patient's action or conduct rather than direct communication. For instance, informed consent can come from a patient's nodding of the head, or by them showing up at the agreed-upon time for surgery.</p>
</div>

<button class="accordion">What is expressed consent?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Express consent happens when the patient directly communicates their valid consent verbally or in writing to the doctor or healthcare provider.</p>
</div>

